    Class Description
    API
    Represents the entire DMBook API.
    APIFormatUtility
    This utility class helps standardize the formatting of API responses into stringified versions of certain response types.
    CharacterAPI
    This endpoint is responsible for handling all data related to characters for DMBook.
    CharacterList
    A servlet to handle CRUD for the character list.
    Characters
    The Characters class is really supposed to be the Character class, but Character is also a significant type in Java, so I made this classname plural.
    CharactersDaoTest
    This test suite utilizes the generic DAO to test all functionality related to the characters database table
    CognitoJWTParser
    Utility class for all operations on JWT.
    CognitoTokenHeader  
    CorsFilter
    This utility exists to filter all requests, and specifically to add appropriate headers to thoroughly allow cross origin resource sharing (CORS)
    Database
    Provides access the database Created on 8/31/16.
    Encounter
    The Encounter class represents a singular planned encounter in a Dungeons and Dragons game.
    EncounterAPI
    This endpoint is responsible for handling all data related to encounters for DMBook.
    EncounterList
    A testing/utility type class that just lists all encounters in the database.
    GenericDao<T>
    A generic DAO somewhat inspired by http://rodrigouchoa.wordpress.com
    GetAllResponse
    The GetAllResponse represents the data received from the DND 5e API when requesting all of a certain endpoint/data type.
    GetAllResponseItem
    This represents a single item in the results array returned by the DND 5e API.
    Keys  
    KeysItem  
    Monster
    The Monster class represents a singular monster from the DND 5e API.
    MonsterAPI
    Represents and organizes the endpoints related to Monsters.
    MonsterDao
    This DAO specifically handles the retrieval of monster data from the DND API.
    MonsterDaoTest
    This tests the MonsterDao class, which both retrieves all monsters in the DND 5e API, and specific monsters.
    MonsterList
    A testing/utility type class that just lists all monsters in the DND 5e API.
    PropertiesLoader
    This interface contains a default method that can be used anywhere a Properties object is needed to be loaded.
    SessionFactoryProvider
    This file provides a SessionFactory for use with DAOs using Hibernate
    TokenResponse  
    User
    The User object
    UserAPI
    This endpoint is responsible for handling all data related to users for DMBook.
    UserDaoTest
    This test suite tests the User class using a generic dao
    UserData
    This class contains a list of all monsters (via the DND 5e API) as well as all characters and encounters belonging to a validated user.
